caption: Very very yummy. Great service. Fair prices. Very nice atmosphere. Clean bathrooms. A++++ all the way and back.

Amazing Mediterranean eatery! Our servers Bashar and Mr. German were very attentive and kind. The service we received from them was first class. Extremely superb service! I highly recommend for the food and service received from all staff! Such a nice restaurant!

Excellent Arab fare in a pretty, upscale setting with excellent, old school service. Bayside is home to the famous Balady's market, so start there to admire the exotic ingredients that will appear in Tanoreen's gourmet dishes. If you like turmeric, sumac, cloves and sesame with your eggplant, lamb and hummos dishes you will love this food. We will be back, looking forward to dining outdoors in warmer weather too.

Hands down this was one of the best dining experiences I've ever had. I'm from the Caribbean so my standards for flavorful food that tastes like someone put their soul into it is pretty high! I'll keep it short; every single item I tasted was beyond delicious and abundantly seasoned to perfection. Cocktails were above expectations; unique flavors of martinis with very generous pours of alcohol. Service was extremely attentive and we never had to chase down our servers. Our table was consistently cleaned off. The zaatar chips; amazing, and I placed an order of it to go so I could eat my leftover hummus the next day. Knafeh was scrumptious! This is definitely my new favorite restaurant in Brooklyn!!!
Excellent service and great food. An enjoyable experience throughout. Our waiter was attentive but not overwhelming. The eggplant dish was fantastic with a unique blend of flavors. A must visit.

Highly recommend for a slightly expensive but very worth it meal!

Five stars for service that is welcoming and allows diners to enjoy a leisurely meal. But three stars because after two visits and one delivery,  I can't really describe anything I ate. Everything was adequate but nothing was a stand out.

You are the parsley to my tabbouleh. That’s just how I feel about Tanoreen.  A true middle eastern out of this world experience. As soon as you walk in you’re instantly transported elsewhere.  Came with a large group of friends and my mind was blown away by the amazing dishes. The best way to order is to get a little bit of everything family style, that way you can try it all! (Next time I have to make sure our whole group is vegetarian so we can order more hehe)  Everything is fresh and homemade. Ordered the vegetarian platter with a mix of things. Grape leaves were sooooo sooo good. Side of falafel, hummus and baba ghanouge. Like my mouth is still salivating from all the goodness. Wish this place was closer to me so I could be here every day.  Can’t wait to go back for more! Great for all diets (VEG, GF, V)

Rough experience. Upon entry at 4pm with no reservation on a Sunday to an empty restaurant the host kindly says "since you don't have a reservation, we would just need you out by 6pm", literally the first thing we hear when we come in. Negative experience upon entry. Service was satisfactory, until I asked if the feta salad was fresh. The Tomatoes tasted like the salad was prepared the day before, soggy and oversaturated in vinegar. Server said it had just been made and took the salad away. Few minutes later, older lady perhaps owner/manager came out and said there's no way the salad is old it just happened to be something we didn't enjoy. I kindly explained to her I eat this cuisine often and know when the salad may be old. She replies she did notice they were overly ripe and should have been in a soup instead of a salad and said she fixed the issue. I ordered another salad, same issue. I haven't been to the place in a few years, boy has it gone backwards. Much better Mediterranean food out there. Sad experience overall.

We ordered the mouhamara, pastry plate, fetti chicken and the grill combo.  The mouhamara was very watered down, no strong red bell peppers taste or pomegranate sauce.  The pastry was not made fresh, it was simply heated.  The fetti was the most edible of the dishes but it was too much rice not enough yogurt.  The grill combo was dry and not appealing, it looked like a mess on a plate.  The service was good, attentive and respectful.

The entire experience is very disappointing actually

If you google Tanoreen it gets an overall star rating of 4.3... I am glad to report this restaurant Tanoreen gets a 5 star rating from me... This was my first time dining at Tanoreen. I was with friends. One friend had previously dined at Tanoreen and raved about it...I must tell you that I have had some middle eastern food in the past but I must say NOTHING like the food I had from Tanoreen. EVERYTHING we ate was DELICIOUS....when I say everything I mean EVERYTHING! We could hardly breathe when we left. I want to share with you that it felt like "Home". First, everyone we interacted with was most kind and gracious especially Jumana who is the daughter of Rawia and Rawia is behind all the deliciousness you will taste. Jumana was wonderful and so appreciative of the feed back I gave her about the food. I told her there was a familiarness about the food like a "Home" feeling as if mom made it... and mom did make it! Please go see and taste for yourself. I will only suggest that you make a reservation. I gets quite packed quickly. Save yourself some aggravation and use the valet service too. Parking is a little challenging but I PROMISE it will be ALL WORTH IT!

Disappointing. After reading all the great reviews, I thought we'd have an amazing meal here, but what we had was lackluster at best. The chicken was very dry. I ordered my lamb medium rare and it came very well done. One of the servers was so wonderful, it's a shame we only saw him once. Everyone else seemed like they didn't care to be there.  We arrived at 3:30 which is definitely super early, but it was just how our day turned out. We were the only people in the restaurant which was fine. The host was eating, also fine, that's perfectly normal, especially for that time of day. What, wasn't fine, was that he seemed annoyed to seat us. I said hello with a smile and he just looked at me while grabbing menus and said nothing. He walked us to a table without ever saying a word! Strangely, we were seated directly next to the servers station which was less than ideal. Again, we were the ONLY people there and could have been seated anywhere, but, instead, had to listen to the staff gathered around the server's station chit chatting and playing around the whole time we were there. It's not to say they were so loud that they disrupted us. It's just that it gave us too clear of a picture of "behind the scenes" and we just felt awkward and out of place. The service was prompt which was definitely a positive. Except for once we got our food, we felt ignored. As I mentioned earlier in the post, the chicken was very dry, clearly overcooked. The lamb that I ordered medium rare, was officially well done. I have attached a picture to show it. As we left, we walked past three individual people who ignored us completely. We walked directly past each of them and they acted like we didn't exist!! I even tried to make eye contact to say thank you but was unsuccessful which was genuinely shocking. How hard is it to say, "thank you" to guests as they are leaving?? Or, "have a good night"? I was exasperated at that point.  The conclusion? Extremely disappointing. We will not be returning and will discourage others as well (if asked our opinion or for a suggestion in the area). Such a shame as there seemed to be success in the past. Those days are CLEARLY behind them.
